                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2572: Telegram (part air)</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Emmet</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-12T13:00:00+01:19"
                            >August 12, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 13—6:33 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. The Netherlands Government’s reply to French <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi>
                    in respect to non-intervention in the Spanish conflict gives assurances that
                    pending the conclusion of a collective agreement it will not give permission,
                    within the frame of existing Dutch law, for the export or transit of arms and
                    ammunition to Spain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Emmet</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
